>I have a 1957 single cab. I recently changed the hand shifter and reverse
>lock out plate ( as the old shifter was worn to the point that the ball on
>the bottom freely rotated and the shift play was very loose). I put in a
>stock shifter and plate bolted it in and its was normal. Nice and snug, but
>it won't go into reverse. Reverse worked fine with the old sloppy shifter
>but the new one won't work. I tried loosening the bolts off but nothing? So
>I swapped another plate and shifter from my other '57 bus. Same thing, no
>reverse.

Replace the coupling out back and the shifter rod bushings. Readjust. Worse 
case the nose cone of the tranny may be worn.




